datasets.name: 6021fab7
queryLines:
SELECT 
    grantee,
    privilege_type
FROM 
    system.information_schema.schema_privileges
WHERE 
    concat(catalog_name, '.', schema_name) = :catalog_schema_name;

datasets.name: 44fcf105
queryLines:
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN :granularity = 'Yearly' THEN DATE_TRUNC('year', event_time)
        WHEN :granularity = 'Monthly' THEN DATE_TRUNC('month', event_time)
        WHEN :granularity = 'Weekly' THEN DATE_TRUNC('week', event_time)
        WHEN :granularity = 'Daily' THEN DATE_TRUNC('day', event_time)
        ELSE DATE_TRUNC('day', event_time) -- default to daily if no match
    END AS usage_date,
    COUNT(*) AS usage_count
FROM 
    system.access.table_lineage
WHERE 
    (concat(source_table_catalog, '.', source_table_schema) = :catalog_schema_name
    OR concat(target_table_catalog, '.', target_table_schema) = :catalog_schema_name) AND
    (event_time >= :date_range_start AND event_time <= :date_range_end )
GROUP BY 
    usage_date
ORDER BY 
    usage_date;

datasets.name: 1b13ae14
queryLines:
SELECT DISTINCT
    lat.source_table_full_name AS dependency,
    ist.table_owner AS owner_name
FROM 
    system.access.table_lineage lat
INNER JOIN
    system.information_schema.tables ist
ON 
    lat.source_table_full_name = CONCAT(ist.TABLE_CATALOG, '.', ist.TABLE_SCHEMA, '.', ist.TABLE_NAME)
WHERE 
    concat(lat.target_table_catalog, '.', lat.target_table_schema) = :catalog_schema_name AND
    (lat.event_time >= :date_range_start AND lat.event_time <= :date_range_end ) AND
    lat.source_table_full_name IS NOT NULL;

datasets.name: a172531b
queryLines:
SELECT
    CASE
        WHEN created_by IS NOT NULL THEN created_by 
    END AS user,
    CASE
        WHEN created_by IS NOT NULL THEN COUNT(*)
    END AS read_count
FROM 
    system.access.table_lineage
WHERE 
    concat(source_table_catalog, '.', source_table_schema) = :catalog_schema_name AND
    (event_time >= :date_range_start AND event_time <= :date_range_end ) AND created_by IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY 
    created_by
ORDER BY 
    read_count DESC
LIMIT 100;

datasets.name: 5365cfed
queryLines:
SELECT
    CASE
        WHEN created_by IS NOT NULL THEN created_by 
    END AS user,
    CASE
        WHEN created_by IS NOT NULL THEN COUNT(*)
    END AS write_count
FROM 
    system.access.table_lineage
WHERE
    concat(target_table_catalog, '.', target_table_schema) = :catalog_schema_name AND
    (event_time >= :date_range_start AND event_time <= :date_range_end ) AND created_by IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY 
    created_by
ORDER BY 
    write_count DESC
LIMIT 100;

datasets.name: 92fbe671
queryLines:
SELECT DISTINCT
    CONCAT(CATALOG_NAME, '.', SCHEMA_NAME) AS catalog_schema
FROM
    system.information_schema.schemata
WHERE
    SCHEMA_NAME IS NOT NULL

datasets.name: 5b9d38ad
queryLines:
SELECT "Yearly" as granularity
UNION ALL
SELECT "Monthly"
UNION ALL
SELECT "Weekly"
UNION ALL
SELECT "Daily"

datasets.name: 64b1c381
queryLines:
SELECT DISTINCT
    lat.entity_id AS dependency,
    lat.created_by AS owner_name,
    CASE
        WHEN lat.entity_type = 'DBSQL_DASHBOARD' THEN 'Legacy Dashboard'
        WHEN lat.entity_type = 'DBSQL_QUERY' THEN 'SQL Query'
        WHEN lat.entity_type = 'DASHBOARD_V3' THEN 'Dashboard'
        WHEN lat.entity_type = 'PIPELINE' THEN 'Pipeline'
        WHEN lat.entity_type = 'JOB' THEN 'Job'
        WHEN lat.entity_type = 'NOTEBOOK' THEN 'Notebook'
        ELSE lat.entity_type
    END AS dependency_type
FROM 
    system.access.table_lineage lat
WHERE 
    concat(lat.target_table_catalog, '.', lat.target_table_schema) = :catalog_schema_name AND
    (lat.event_time >= :date_range_start AND lat.event_time <= :date_range_end ) AND
    lat.source_table_full_name IS NULL AND lat.entity_id IS NOT NULL;
